ABOUT THE SOURCE COURSE MATERIAL
--------------------------------

The University of Manchester COMP11212 course material — including but not
limited to the chapter notes, the wording of exercises and examples, exercise
solutions, exam papers, slide decks, and lecture transcripts — is © The
University of Manchester (and its individual authors). This project does NOT
redistribute that material in any form.

What this project DOES contain that references the course:

  - Numbered references such as "Example 7" or "Exercise 14" used as
    NAVIGATION LABELS so a student studying the course can find the
    matching playground entry quickly.

  - Chapter groupings ("Chapter 2 — Small-step semantics", etc.) used
    as NAVIGATION CATEGORIES that mirror the course's organisation.

These references and groupings are factual labels, not reproductions of the
copyrighted course material itself. The full text of the exercises, the
problem prompts, the explanatory prose, and the official solutions are NOT
included here. Students should refer to the official UoM course materials
(distributed by the University) for the actual exercise text, problem
statements, and chapter exposition.

